From f0adc0cc15ad765b8977562b60ca0aca1186c18a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Johnny Mnemonic <jm@machine-hall.org>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:24:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "vdso/vsyscall: Gate update_vsyscall() behind
 CONFIG_GENERIC_GETTIMEOFDAY"

ia64 selects GENERIC_TIME_VSYSCALL despite having own versions of
update_vsyscall[_tz]() in arch/ia64/kernel/time.c.

As long as ia64 is not switched to the generic vDSO library the old guard
GENERIC_TIME_VSYSCALL needs to stay avoid the empty definitions for
update_vsyscall[_tz](), as the "replacement" GENERIC_GETTIMEOFDAY
requires HAVE_GENERIC_VDSO, too.

This reverts commit bf8f968a63159661acc20254ccdf0dc3c9f1bac2.
---
 include/linux/timekeeper_internal.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/timekeeper_internal.h b/include/linux/timekeeper_internal.h
index 4486dfd5d0de..e36d11e33e0c 100644
--- a/include/linux/timekeeper_internal.h
+++ b/include/linux/timekeeper_internal.h
@@ -190,7 +190,7 @@ struct timekeeper {
 	s32			tai_offset;
 };
 
-#ifdef CONFIG_GENERIC_GETTIMEOFDAY
+#ifdef CONFIG_GENERIC_TIME_VSYSCALL
 
 extern void update_vsyscall(struct timekeeper *tk);
 extern void update_vsyscall_tz(void);
-- 
2.25.1

